static s32 e1000_acquire_nvm_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_acquire_nvm_82575 - Request for access to EEPROM : pointer to the HW structure

Acquire the necessary semaphores for exclusive access to the EEPROM. Set the EEPROM access request bit and wait for EEPROM access grant bit. Return successful if access grant bit set, else clear the request for EEPROM access and return -E1000_ERR_NVM (-1).

e1000_82575.c 파일의 977 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

978 {
979  s32 ret_val = E1000_SUCCESS;
980 
981  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_acquire_nvm_82575");
982 
983  ret_val = e1000_acquire_swfw_sync_82575(hw, E1000_SWFW_EEP_SM);
984  if (ret_val)
985  goto out;
986 
987  /*
988  * Check if there is some access
989  * error this access may hook on
990  */
991  if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i350) {
992  u32 eecd = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_EECD);
993  if (eecd & (E1000_EECD_BLOCKED | E1000_EECD_ABORT |
994  E1000_EECD_TIMEOUT)) {
995  /* Clear all access error flags */
996  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_EECD, eecd |
997  E1000_EECD_ERROR_CLR);
998  DEBUGOUT("Nvm bit banging access error detected and cleared.\n");
999  }
1000  }
1001 
1002  if (hw->mac.type == e1000_82580) {
1003  u32 eecd = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_EECD);
1004  if (eecd & E1000_EECD_BLOCKED) {
1005  /* Clear access error flag */
1006  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_EECD, eecd |
1007  E1000_EECD_BLOCKED);

1009  }
1010  }
1011

1013  if (ret_val)
1014  e1000_release_swfw_sync_82575(hw, E1000_SWFW_EEP_SM);

1016 out:

1018 }

static s32 e1000_acquire_swfw_sync_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw,
u16  mask 
)
static

e1000_acquire_swfw_sync_82575 - Acquire SW/FW semaphore : pointer to the HW structure : specifies which semaphore to acquire

Acquire the SW/FW semaphore to access the PHY or NVM. The mask will also specify which port we're acquiring the lock for.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 1044 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

1045 {
1046  u32 swfw_sync;
1047  u32 swmask = mask;
1048  u32 fwmask = mask << 16;
1049  s32 ret_val = E1000_SUCCESS;
1050  s32 i = 0, timeout = 200;
1051 
1052  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_acquire_swfw_sync_82575");
1053 
1054  while (i < timeout) {
1055  if (e1000_get_hw_semaphore_generic(hw)) {
1056  ret_val = -E1000_ERR_SWFW_SYNC;
1057  goto out;
1058  }
1059 
1060  swfw_sync = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_SW_FW_SYNC);
1061  if (!(swfw_sync & (fwmask | swmask)))
1062  break;
1063 
1064  /*
1065  * Firmware currently using resource (fwmask)
1066  * or other software thread using resource (swmask)
1067  */
1068  e1000_put_hw_semaphore_generic(hw);
1069  msec_delay_irq(5);
1070  i++;
1071  }
1072 
1073  if (i == timeout) {
1074  DEBUGOUT("Driver can't access resource, SW_FW_SYNC timeout.\n");
1075  ret_val = -E1000_ERR_SWFW_SYNC;
1076  goto out;
1077  }
1078 
1079  swfw_sync |= swmask;
1080  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_SW_FW_SYNC, swfw_sync);
1081 
1082  e1000_put_hw_semaphore_generic(hw);
1083 
1084 out:
1085  return ret_val;
1086 }

static s32 e1000_check_for_link_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_check_for_link_82575 - Check for link : pointer to the HW structure

If sgmii is enabled, then use the pcs register to determine link, otherwise use the generic interface for determining link.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 1186 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

1187 {
1188  s32 ret_val;
1189  u16 speed, duplex;
1190 
1191  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_check_for_link_82575");
1192 
1193  if (hw->phy.media_type != e1000_media_type_copper) {
1194  ret_val = e1000_get_pcs_speed_and_duplex_82575(hw, &speed,
1195  &duplex);
1196  /*
1197  * Use this flag to determine if link needs to be checked or
1198  * not. If we have link clear the flag so that we do not

1217 }

1234  /* Check for copper. */
1235  ret_val = phy->ops.write_reg(hw, E1000_M88E1112_PAGE_ADDR, 0);
1236  if (ret_val)
1237  return ret_val;
1238 
1239  ret_val = phy->ops.read_reg(hw, E1000_M88E1112_STATUS, &data);
1240  if (ret_val)
1241  return ret_val;
1242 
1243  if (data & E1000_M88E1112_STATUS_LINK)
1244  port = E1000_MEDIA_PORT_COPPER;
1245 
1246  /* Check for other. */
1247  ret_val = phy->ops.write_reg(hw, E1000_M88E1112_PAGE_ADDR, 1);
1248  if (ret_val)
1249  return ret_val;
1250 
1251  ret_val = phy->ops.read_reg(hw, E1000_M88E1112_STATUS, &data);
1252  if (ret_val)
1253  return ret_val;
1254 
1255  if (data & E1000_M88E1112_STATUS_LINK)
1256  port = E1000_MEDIA_PORT_OTHER;
1257 
1258  /* Determine if a swap needs to happen. */
1259  if (port && (hw->dev_spec._82575.media_port != port)) {
1260  hw->dev_spec._82575.media_port = port;
1261  hw->dev_spec._82575.media_changed = true;
1262  }
1263 
1264  if (port == E1000_MEDIA_PORT_COPPER) {
1265  /* reset page to 0 */
1266  ret_val = phy->ops.write_reg(hw, E1000_M88E1112_PAGE_ADDR, 0);
1267  if (ret_val)
1268  return ret_val;
1269  e1000_check_for_link_82575(hw);
1270  } else {
1271  e1000_check_for_link_82575(hw);
1272  /* reset page to 0 */
1273  ret_val = phy->ops.write_reg(hw, E1000_M88E1112_PAGE_ADDR, 0);
1274  if (ret_val)
1275  return ret_val;
1276  }
1277 
1278  return E1000_SUCCESS;
1279 }

static s32 e1000_get_cfg_done_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_get_cfg_done_82575 - Read config done bit : pointer to the HW structure

Read the management control register for the config done bit for completion status. NOTE: silicon which is EEPROM-less will fail trying to read the config done bit, so an error is ONLY logged and returns E1000_SUCCESS. If we were to return with error, EEPROM-less silicon would not be able to be reset or change link.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 1122 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

1125  u32 mask = E1000_NVM_CFG_DONE_PORT_0;
1126 
1127  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_get_cfg_done_82575");
1128 
1129  if (hw->bus.func == E1000_FUNC_1)

1132  mask = E1000_NVM_CFG_DONE_PORT_2;

Clocks in/out one bit via I2C data/clock

3440 {
3441  s32 status = E1000_SUCCESS;
3442  u32 i = 0;
3443  u32 i2cctl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_I2CPARAMS);
3444  u32 timeout = 10;

3449  e1000_raise_i2c_clk(hw, &i2cctl);
3450 
3451  /* Minimum high period of clock is 4us */
3452  usec_delay(E1000_I2C_T_HIGH);
3453 
3454  /* Wait until SCL returns high */

3471

3474

3476 }

static s32 e1000_get_media_type_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_get_media_type_82575 - derives current media type. : pointer to the HW structure

The media type is chosen reflecting few settings. The following are taken into account:

  • link mode set in the current port Init Control Word #3
  • current link mode settings in CSR register
  • MDIO vs. I2C PHY control interface chosen
  • SFP module media type

e1000_82575.c 파일의 1768 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

1769 {
1770  struct e1000_dev_spec_82575 *dev_spec = &hw->dev_spec._82575;
1771  s32 ret_val = E1000_SUCCESS;
1772  u32 ctrl_ext = 0;
1773  u32 link_mode = 0;
1774 
1775  /* Set internal phy as default */
1776  dev_spec->sgmii_active = false;
1777  dev_spec->module_plugged = false;
1778 
1779  /* Get CSR setting */
1780  ctrl_ext = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT);
1781 
1782  /* extract link mode setting */
1783  link_mode = ctrl_ext & E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_MASK;
1784 
1785  switch (link_mode) {
1786  case E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_1000BASE_KX:
1787  hw->phy.media_type = e1000_media_type_internal_serdes;
1788  break;
1789  case E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_GMII:
1790  hw->phy.media_type = e1000_media_type_copper;
1791  break;
1792  case E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_SGMII:
1793  /* Get phy control interface type set (MDIO vs. I2C)*/
1794  if (e1000_sgmii_uses_mdio_82575(hw)) {
1795  hw->phy.media_type = e1000_media_type_copper;
1796  dev_spec->sgmii_active = true;
1797  break;
1798  }
1799  /* fall through for I2C based SGMII */
1800  case E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_PCIE_SERDES:
1801  /* read media type from SFP EEPROM */
1802 #ifdef I2C_ENABLED
1803  printk(KERN_INFO "igb_avb I2C enabled - set_sfp_media_type_82575() called");
1804  ret_val = e1000_set_sfp_media_type_82575(hw);
1805 #else
1806  printk(KERN_INFO "igb_avb I2C disabled - set_sfp_media_type_82575() not necessary");
1807  hw->phy.media_type = e1000_media_type_unknown;
1808 #endif
1809  if ((ret_val != E1000_SUCCESS) ||
1810  (hw->phy.media_type == e1000_media_type_unknown)) {
1811  /*
1812  * If media type was not identified then return media
1813  * type defined by the CTRL_EXT settings.
1814  */
1815  hw->phy.media_type = e1000_media_type_internal_serdes;
1816 
1817  if (link_mode == E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_SGMII) {
1818  hw->phy.media_type = e1000_media_type_copper;
1819  dev_spec->sgmii_active = true;
1820  }
1821 
1822  break;
1823  }
1824 
1825  /* do not change link mode for 100BaseFX */
1826  if (dev_spec->eth_flags.e100_base_fx)
1827  break;
1828 
1829  /* change current link mode setting */
1830  ctrl_ext &= ~E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_MASK;
1831 
1832  if (hw->phy.media_type == e1000_media_type_copper)
1833  ctrl_ext |= E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_SGMII;
1834  else
1835  ctrl_ext |= E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_PCIE_SERDES;
1836 
1837  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT, ctrl_ext);
1838 
1839  break;
1840  }
1841 
1842  return ret_val;
1843 }

1325 
1326  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_get_pcs_speed_and_duplex_82575");
1327 
1328  /*
1329  * Read the PCS Status register for link state. For non-copper mode,
1330  * the status register is not accurate. The PCS status register is
1331  * used instead.
1332  */
1333  pcs = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PCS_LSTAT);
1334 
1335  /*
1336  * The link up bit determines when link is up on autoneg.
1337  */
1338  if (pcs & E1000_PCS_LSTS_LINK_OK) {
1339  mac->serdes_has_link = true;
1340 
1341  /* Detect and store PCS speed */
1342  if (pcs & E1000_PCS_LSTS_SPEED_1000)
1343  *speed = SPEED_1000;
1344  else if (pcs & E1000_PCS_LSTS_SPEED_100)
1345  *speed = SPEED_100;
1346  else
1347  *speed = SPEED_10;
1348 
1349  /* Detect and store PCS duplex */
1350  if (pcs & E1000_PCS_LSTS_DUPLEX_FULL)
1351  *duplex = FULL_DUPLEX;
1352  else
1353  *duplex = HALF_DUPLEX;
1354 
1355  /* Check if it is an I354 2.5Gb backplane connection. */
1356  if (mac->type == e1000_i354) {
1357  status = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_STATUS);
1358  if ((status & E1000_STATUS_2P5_SKU) &&
1359  !(status & E1000_STATUS_2P5_SKU_OVER)) {
1360  *speed = SPEED_2500;
1361  *duplex = FULL_DUPLEX;
1362  DEBUGOUT("2500 Mbs, ");
1363  DEBUGOUT("Full Duplex\n");
1364  }
1365  }
1366 
1367  } else {
1368  mac->serdes_has_link = false;
1369  *speed = 0;
1370  *duplex = 0;
1371  }
1372 
1373  return E1000_SUCCESS;
1374 }

static s32 e1000_get_phy_id_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_get_phy_id_82575 - Retrieve PHY addr and id : pointer to the HW structure

Retrieves the PHY address and ID for both PHY's which do and do not use sgmi interface.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 652 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

653 {
654  struct e1000_phy_info *phy = &hw->phy;
655  s32 ret_val = E1000_SUCCESS;
656  u16 phy_id;
657  u32 ctrl_ext;
658  u32 mdic;
659 
660  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_get_phy_id_82575");
661 
662  /* some i354 devices need an extra read for phy id */
663  if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i354)
664  e1000_get_phy_id(hw);
665 
666  /*
667  * For SGMII PHYs, we try the list of possible addresses until
668  * we find one that works. For non-SGMII PHYs
669  * (e.g. integrated copper PHYs), an address of 1 should
670  * work. The result of this function should mean phy->phy_addr
671  * and phy->id are set correctly.
672  */
673  if (!e1000_sgmii_active_82575(hw)) {
674  phy->addr = 1;
675  ret_val = e1000_get_phy_id(hw);
676  goto out;
677  }
678 
679  if (e1000_sgmii_uses_mdio_82575(hw)) {
680  switch (hw->mac.type) {
681  case e1000_82575:
682  case e1000_82576:
683  mdic = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_MDIC);
684  mdic &= E1000_MDIC_PHY_MASK;
685  phy->addr = mdic >> E1000_MDIC_PHY_SHIFT;
686  break;
687  case e1000_82580:
688  case e1000_i350:
689  case e1000_i354:
690  case e1000_i210:
691  case e1000_i211:
692  mdic = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_MDICNFG);
693  mdic &= E1000_MDICNFG_PHY_MASK;
694  phy->addr = mdic >> E1000_MDICNFG_PHY_SHIFT;
695  break;
696  default:
697  ret_val = -E1000_ERR_PHY;
698  goto out;
699  break;
700  }
701  ret_val = e1000_get_phy_id(hw);
702  goto out;
703  }
704 
705  /* Power on sgmii phy if it is disabled */
706  ctrl_ext = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT);
707  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT,
708  ctrl_ext & ~E1000_CTRL_EXT_SDP3_DATA);
709  E1000_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
710  msec_delay(300);
711 
712  /*
713  * The address field in the I2CCMD register is 3 bits and 0 is invalid.
714  * Therefore, we need to test 1-7
715  */
716  for (phy->addr = 1; phy->addr < 8; phy->addr++) {
717  ret_val = e1000_read_phy_reg_sgmii_82575(hw, PHY_ID1, &phy_id);
718  if (ret_val == E1000_SUCCESS) {
719  DEBUGOUT2("Vendor ID 0x%08X read at address %u\n",
720  phy_id, phy->addr);
721  /*
722  * At the time of this writing, The M88 part is
723  * the only supported SGMII PHY product.
724  */
725  if (phy_id == M88_VENDOR)
726  break;
727  } else {
728  DEBUGOUT1("PHY address %u was unreadable\n",
729  phy->addr);
730  }
731  }
732 
733  /* A valid PHY type couldn't be found. */
734  if (phy->addr == 8) {
735  phy->addr = 0;
736  ret_val = -E1000_ERR_PHY;
737  } else {
738  ret_val = e1000_get_phy_id(hw);
739  }
740 
741  /* restore previous sfp cage power state */
742  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT, ctrl_ext);
743 
744 out:
745  return ret_val;
746 }

void e1000_i2c_bus_clear ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)

e1000_i2c_bus_clear - Clears the I2C bus : pointer to hardware structure

Clears the I2C bus by sending nine clock pulses. Used when data line is stuck low.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 3645 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

3657  e1000_raise_i2c_clk(hw, &i2cctl);

static void e1000_i2c_stop ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_i2c_stop - Sets I2C stop condition : pointer to hardware structure

Sets I2C stop condition (Low -> High on SDA while SCL is High)

e1000_82575.c 파일의 3358 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

3359 {
3360  u32 i2cctl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_I2CPARAMS);
3361 
3362  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_i2c_stop");
3363 
3364  /* Stop condition must begin with data low and clock high */
3365  e1000_set_i2c_data(hw, &i2cctl, 0);
3366  e1000_raise_i2c_clk(hw, &i2cctl);
3367 
3368  /* Setup time for stop condition (4us) */
3369  usec_delay(E1000_I2C_T_SU_STO);
3370 
3371  e1000_set_i2c_data(hw, &i2cctl, 1);
3372 
3373  /* bus free time between stop and start (4.7us)*/
3374  usec_delay(E1000_I2C_T_BUF);
3375 }

s32 e1000_init_hw_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)

e1000_init_hw_82575 - Initialize hardware : pointer to the HW structure

This inits the hardware readying it for operation.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 1482 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

1483 {
1484  struct e1000_mac_info *mac = &hw->mac;
1485  s32 ret_val;
1486  u16 i, rar_count = mac->rar_entry_count;
1487 
1488  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_init_hw_82575");
1489 
1490  /* Initialize identification LED */
1491  ret_val = mac->ops.id_led_init(hw);
1492  if (ret_val) {
1493  DEBUGOUT("Error initializing identification LED\n");
1494  /* This is not fatal and we should not stop init due to this */
1495  }
1496 
1497  /* Disabling VLAN filtering */
1498  DEBUGOUT("Initializing the IEEE VLAN\n");
1499  mac->ops.clear_vfta(hw);
1500 
1501  /* Setup the receive address */
1502  e1000_init_rx_addrs_generic(hw, rar_count);
1503 
1504  /* Zero out the Multicast HASH table */
1505  DEBUGOUT("Zeroing the MTA\n");
1506  for (i = 0; i < mac->mta_reg_count; i++)
1507  E1000_WRITE_REG_ARRAY(hw, E1000_MTA, i, 0);
1508 
1509  /* Zero out the Unicast HASH table */
1510  DEBUGOUT("Zeroing the UTA\n");
1511  for (i = 0; i < mac->uta_reg_count; i++)
1512  E1000_WRITE_REG_ARRAY(hw, E1000_UTA, i, 0);
1513 
1514  /* Setup link and flow control */
1515  ret_val = mac->ops.setup_link(hw);
1516 
1517  /* Set the default MTU size */
1518  hw->dev_spec._82575.mtu = 1500;
1519 
1520  /*
1521  * Clear all of the statistics registers (clear on read). It is
1522  * important that we do this after we have tried to establish link
1523  * because the symbol error count will increment wildly if there
1524  * is no link.
1525  */
1526  e1000_clear_hw_cntrs_82575(hw);
1527 
1528  return ret_val;
1529 }

static s32 e1000_init_mac_params_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_init_mac_params_82575 - Init MAC func ptrs. : pointer to the HW structure

e1000_82575.c 파일의 401 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

402 {
403  struct e1000_mac_info *mac = &hw->mac;
404  struct e1000_dev_spec_82575 *dev_spec = &hw->dev_spec._82575;
405 
406  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_init_mac_params_82575");
407 
408  /* Derives media type */
409  e1000_get_media_type_82575(hw);
410  /* Set mta register count */
411  mac->mta_reg_count = 128;
412  /* Set uta register count */
413  mac->uta_reg_count = (hw->mac.type == e1000_82575) ? 0 : 128;
414  /* Set rar entry count */
415  mac->rar_entry_count = E1000_RAR_ENTRIES_82575;
416  if (mac->type == e1000_82576)
417  mac->rar_entry_count = E1000_RAR_ENTRIES_82576;
418  if (mac->type == e1000_82580)
419  mac->rar_entry_count = E1000_RAR_ENTRIES_82580;
420  if (mac->type == e1000_i350 || mac->type == e1000_i354)
421  mac->rar_entry_count = E1000_RAR_ENTRIES_I350;
422 
423  /* Enable EEE default settings for EEE supported devices */
424  if (mac->type >= e1000_i350)
425  dev_spec->eee_disable = false;
426 
427  /* Allow a single clear of the SW semaphore on I210 and newer */
428  if (mac->type >= e1000_i210)
429  dev_spec->clear_semaphore_once = true;
430 
431  /* Set if part includes ASF firmware */
432  mac->asf_firmware_present = true;
433  /* FWSM register */
434  mac->has_fwsm = true;
435  /* ARC supported; valid only if manageability features are enabled. */
436  mac->arc_subsystem_valid =
437  !!(E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_FWSM) & E1000_FWSM_MODE_MASK);
438 
439  /* Function pointers */
440 
441  /* bus type/speed/width */
442  mac->ops.get_bus_info = e1000_get_bus_info_pcie_generic;
443  /* reset */
444  if (mac->type >= e1000_82580)
445  mac->ops.reset_hw = e1000_reset_hw_82580;
446  else
447  mac->ops.reset_hw = e1000_reset_hw_82575;
448  /* hw initialization */
449  if ((mac->type == e1000_i210) || (mac->type == e1000_i211))
450  mac->ops.init_hw = e1000_init_hw_i210;
451  else
452  mac->ops.init_hw = e1000_init_hw_82575;
453  /* link setup */
454  mac->ops.setup_link = e1000_setup_link_generic;
455  /* physical interface link setup */
456  mac->ops.setup_physical_interface =
457  (hw->phy.media_type == e1000_media_type_copper)
458  ? e1000_setup_copper_link_82575 : e1000_setup_serdes_link_82575;
459  /* physical interface shutdown */
460  mac->ops.shutdown_serdes = e1000_shutdown_serdes_link_82575;
461  /* physical interface power up */
462  mac->ops.power_up_serdes = e1000_power_up_serdes_link_82575;
463  /* check for link */
464  mac->ops.check_for_link = e1000_check_for_link_82575;
465  /* read mac address */
466  mac->ops.read_mac_addr = e1000_read_mac_addr_82575;
467  /* configure collision distance */
468  mac->ops.config_collision_dist = e1000_config_collision_dist_82575;
469  /* multicast address update */
470  mac->ops.update_mc_addr_list = e1000_update_mc_addr_list_generic;
471  if (hw->mac.type == e1000_i350 || mac->type == e1000_i354) {
472  /* writing VFTA */
473  mac->ops.write_vfta = e1000_write_vfta_i350;
474  /* clearing VFTA */
475  mac->ops.clear_vfta = e1000_clear_vfta_i350;
476  } else {
477  /* writing VFTA */
478  mac->ops.write_vfta = e1000_write_vfta_generic;
479  /* clearing VFTA */
480  mac->ops.clear_vfta = e1000_clear_vfta_generic;
481  }
482  if (hw->mac.type >= e1000_82580)
483  mac->ops.validate_mdi_setting =
484  e1000_validate_mdi_setting_crossover_generic;
485  /* ID LED init */
486  mac->ops.id_led_init = e1000_id_led_init_generic;
487  /* blink LED */
488  mac->ops.blink_led = e1000_blink_led_generic;
489  /* setup LED */
490  mac->ops.setup_led = e1000_setup_led_generic;
491  /* cleanup LED */
492  mac->ops.cleanup_led = e1000_cleanup_led_generic;
493  /* turn on/off LED */
494  mac->ops.led_on = e1000_led_on_generic;
495  mac->ops.led_off = e1000_led_off_generic;
496  /* clear hardware counters */
497  mac->ops.clear_hw_cntrs = e1000_clear_hw_cntrs_82575;
498  /* link info */
499  mac->ops.get_link_up_info = e1000_get_link_up_info_82575;
500  /* get thermal sensor data */
501  mac->ops.get_thermal_sensor_data =
502  e1000_get_thermal_sensor_data_generic;
503  mac->ops.init_thermal_sensor_thresh =
504  e1000_init_thermal_sensor_thresh_generic;
505  /* acquire SW_FW sync */
506  mac->ops.acquire_swfw_sync = e1000_acquire_swfw_sync_82575;
507  mac->ops.release_swfw_sync = e1000_release_swfw_sync_82575;
508  if (mac->type >= e1000_i210) {
509  mac->ops.acquire_swfw_sync = e1000_acquire_swfw_sync_i210;
510  mac->ops.release_swfw_sync = e1000_release_swfw_sync_i210;
511  }
512 
513  /* set lan id for port to determine which phy lock to use */
514  hw->mac.ops.set_lan_id(hw);
515 
516  return E1000_SUCCESS;
517 }

e1000_init_nvm_params_82575 - Init NVM func ptrs. : pointer to the HW structure

e1000_82575.c 파일의 316 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

317 {
318  struct e1000_nvm_info *nvm = &hw->nvm;
319  u32 eecd = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_EECD);
320  u16 size;
321 
322  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_init_nvm_params_82575");
323 
324  size = (u16)((eecd & E1000_EECD_SIZE_EX_MASK) >>
325  E1000_EECD_SIZE_EX_SHIFT);
326  /*
327  * Added to a constant, "size" becomes the left-shift value
328  * for setting word_size.
329  */
330  size += NVM_WORD_SIZE_BASE_SHIFT;
331 
332  /* Just in case size is out of range, cap it to the largest
333  * EEPROM size supported
334  */
335  if (size > 15)
336  size = 15;
337 
338  nvm->word_size = 1 << size;
339  if (hw->mac.type < e1000_i210) {
340  nvm->opcode_bits = 8;
341  nvm->delay_usec = 1;
342 
343  switch (nvm->override) {
344  case e1000_nvm_override_spi_large:
345  nvm->page_size = 32;
346  nvm->address_bits = 16;
347  break;
348  case e1000_nvm_override_spi_small:
349  nvm->page_size = 8;
350  nvm->address_bits = 8;
351  break;
352  default:
353  nvm->page_size = eecd & E1000_EECD_ADDR_BITS ? 32 : 8;
354  nvm->address_bits = eecd & E1000_EECD_ADDR_BITS ?
355  16 : 8;
356  break;
357  }
358  if (nvm->word_size == (1 << 15))
359  nvm->page_size = 128;
360 
361  nvm->type = e1000_nvm_eeprom_spi;
362  } else {
363  nvm->type = e1000_nvm_flash_hw;
364  }
365 
366  /* Function Pointers */
367  nvm->ops.acquire = e1000_acquire_nvm_82575;
368  nvm->ops.release = e1000_release_nvm_82575;
369  if (nvm->word_size < (1 << 15))
370  nvm->ops.read = e1000_read_nvm_eerd;
371  else
372  nvm->ops.read = e1000_read_nvm_spi;
373 
374  nvm->ops.write = e1000_write_nvm_spi;
375  nvm->ops.validate = e1000_validate_nvm_checksum_generic;
376  nvm->ops.update = e1000_update_nvm_checksum_generic;
377  nvm->ops.valid_led_default = e1000_valid_led_default_82575;
378 
379  /* override generic family function pointers for specific descendants */
380  switch (hw->mac.type) {
381  case e1000_82580:
382  nvm->ops.validate = e1000_validate_nvm_checksum_82580;
383  nvm->ops.update = e1000_update_nvm_checksum_82580;
384  break;
385  case e1000_i350:
386  case e1000_i354:
387  nvm->ops.validate = e1000_validate_nvm_checksum_i350;
388  nvm->ops.update = e1000_update_nvm_checksum_i350;
389  break;
390  default:
391  break;
392  }
393 
394  return E1000_SUCCESS;
395 }

s32 e1000_init_thermal_sensor_thresh_generic ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)

e1000_init_thermal_sensor_thresh_generic - Sets thermal sensor thresholds : pointer to hardware structure

Sets the thermal sensor thresholds according to the NVM map and save off the threshold and location values into mac.thermal_sensor_data

e1000_82575.c 파일의 3748 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

3749 {
3750  u16 ets_offset;
3751  u16 ets_cfg;
3752  u16 ets_sensor;
3753  u8 low_thresh_delta;
3754  u8 num_sensors;
3755  u8 sensor_index;
3756  u8 sensor_location;
3757  u8 therm_limit;
3758  u8 i;
3759  struct e1000_thermal_sensor_data *data = &hw->mac.thermal_sensor_data;
3760 
3761  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_init_thermal_sensor_thresh_generic");
3762 
3763  if ((hw->mac.type != e1000_i350) || (hw->bus.func != 0))
3764  return E1000_NOT_IMPLEMENTED;
3765 
3766  memset(data, 0, sizeof(struct e1000_thermal_sensor_data));
3767 
3768  data->sensor[0].location = 0x1;
3769  data->sensor[0].caution_thresh =
3770  (E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_THHIGHTC) & 0xFF);
3771  data->sensor[0].max_op_thresh =
3772  (E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_THLOWTC) & 0xFF);
3773 
3774  /* Return the internal sensor only if ETS is unsupported */
3775  e1000_read_nvm(hw, NVM_ETS_CFG, 1, &ets_offset);
3776  if ((ets_offset == 0x0000) || (ets_offset == 0xFFFF))
3777  return E1000_SUCCESS;
3778 
3779  e1000_read_nvm(hw, ets_offset, 1, &ets_cfg);
3780  if (((ets_cfg & NVM_ETS_TYPE_MASK) >> NVM_ETS_TYPE_SHIFT)
3781  != NVM_ETS_TYPE_EMC)
3782  return E1000_NOT_IMPLEMENTED;
3783 
3784  low_thresh_delta = ((ets_cfg & NVM_ETS_LTHRES_DELTA_MASK) >>
3785  NVM_ETS_LTHRES_DELTA_SHIFT);
3786  num_sensors = (ets_cfg & NVM_ETS_NUM_SENSORS_MASK);
3787 
3788  for (i = 1; i <= num_sensors; i++) {
3789  e1000_read_nvm(hw, (ets_offset + i), 1, &ets_sensor);
3790  sensor_index = ((ets_sensor & NVM_ETS_DATA_INDEX_MASK) >>
3791  NVM_ETS_DATA_INDEX_SHIFT);
3792  sensor_location = ((ets_sensor & NVM_ETS_DATA_LOC_MASK) >>
3793  NVM_ETS_DATA_LOC_SHIFT);
3794  therm_limit = ets_sensor & NVM_ETS_DATA_HTHRESH_MASK;
3795 
3796  hw->phy.ops.write_i2c_byte(hw,
3797  e1000_emc_therm_limit[sensor_index],
3798  E1000_I2C_THERMAL_SENSOR_ADDR,
3799  therm_limit);
3800 
3801  if ((i < E1000_MAX_SENSORS) && (sensor_location != 0)) {
3802  data->sensor[i].location = sensor_location;
3803  data->sensor[i].caution_thresh = therm_limit;
3804  data->sensor[i].max_op_thresh = therm_limit -
3805  low_thresh_delta;
3806  }
3807  }
3808  return E1000_SUCCESS;
3809 }

s32 e1000_initialize_M88E1512_phy ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)

e1000_initialize_M88E1512_phy - Initialize M88E1512 PHY : pointer to the HW structure

Initialize Marverl 1512 to work correctly with Avoton.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 2826 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

2827 {
2828  struct e1000_phy_info *phy = &hw->phy;
2829  s32 ret_val = E1000_SUCCESS;
2830 
2831  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_initialize_M88E1512_phy");
2832 
2833  /* Check if this is correct PHY. */
2834  if (phy->id != M88E1512_E_PHY_ID)
2835  goto out;
2836 
2837  /* Switch to PHY page 0xFF. */
2838  ret_val = phy->ops.write_reg(hw, E1000_M88E1543_PAGE_ADDR, 0x00FF);
2839  if (ret_val)
2840  goto out;
2841

2860  goto out;
2861

2871  if (ret_val)
2872  goto out;
2873

2876  if (ret_val)
2877  goto out;
2878

2880  if (ret_val)
2881  goto out;
2882 
2883  /* Switch to PHY page 0x12. */
2884  ret_val = phy->ops.write_reg(hw, E1000_M88E1543_PAGE_ADDR, 0x12);
2885  if (ret_val)
2886  goto out;
2887 
2888  /* Change mode to SGMII-to-Copper */
2889  ret_val = phy->ops.write_reg(hw, E1000_M88E1512_MODE, 0x8001);
2890  if (ret_val)
2891  goto out;
2892 
2893  /* Return the PHY to page 0. */
2894  ret_val = phy->ops.write_reg(hw, E1000_M88E1543_PAGE_ADDR, 0);
2895  if (ret_val)
2896  goto out;
2897 
2898  ret_val = phy->ops.commit(hw);
2899  if (ret_val) {
2900  DEBUGOUT("Error committing the PHY changes\n");
2901  return ret_val;
2902  }
2903 
2904  msec_delay(1000);
2905 out:
2906  return ret_val;
2907 }

u8  byte_offset,
u8  dev_addr,
u8 *  data 
)

e1000_read_i2c_byte_generic - Reads 8 bit word over I2C : pointer to hardware structure : byte offset to read : device address : value read

Performs byte read operation over I2C interface at a specified device address.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 3169 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

3171 {
3172  s32 status = E1000_SUCCESS;
3173  u32 max_retry = 10;
3174  u32 retry = 1;
3175  u16 swfw_mask = 0;
3176 
3177  bool nack = true;
3178 
3179  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_read_i2c_byte_generic");
3180 
3181  swfw_mask = E1000_SWFW_PHY0_SM;
3182 
3183  do {
3184  if (hw->mac.ops.acquire_swfw_sync(hw, swfw_mask)
3185  != E1000_SUCCESS) {
3186  status = E1000_ERR_SWFW_SYNC;
3187  goto read_byte_out;
3188  }
3189 
3190  e1000_i2c_start(hw);
3191 
3192  /* Device Address and write indication */
3193  status = e1000_clock_out_i2c_byte(hw, dev_addr);
3194  if (status != E1000_SUCCESS)
3195  goto fail;
3196 
3197  status = e1000_get_i2c_ack(hw);
3198  if (status != E1000_SUCCESS)
3199  goto fail;
3200

3202  if (status != E1000_SUCCESS)
3203  goto fail;
3204

3206  if (status != E1000_SUCCESS)
3207  goto fail;
3208

3210 
3211  /* Device Address and read indication */
3212  status = e1000_clock_out_i2c_byte(hw, (dev_addr | 0x1));
3213  if (status != E1000_SUCCESS)
3214  goto fail;
3215 
3216  status = e1000_get_i2c_ack(hw);
3217  if (status != E1000_SUCCESS)
3218  goto fail;
3219 
3220  e1000_clock_in_i2c_byte(hw, data);
3221 
3222  status = e1000_clock_out_i2c_bit(hw, nack);
3223  if (status != E1000_SUCCESS)
3224  goto fail;
3225

3227  break;
3228 
3229 fail:
3230  hw->mac.ops.release_swfw_sync(hw, swfw_mask);
3231  msec_delay(100);
3232  e1000_i2c_bus_clear(hw);
3233  retry++;
3234  if (retry < max_retry)
3235  DEBUGOUT("I2C byte read error - Retrying.\n");
3236  else
3237  DEBUGOUT("I2C byte read error.\n");
3238 
3239  } while (retry < max_retry);
3240 
3241  hw->mac.ops.release_swfw_sync(hw, swfw_mask);
3242 
3243 read_byte_out:
3244 
3245  return status;
3246 }

static

e1000_reset_hw_82575 - Reset hardware : pointer to the HW structure

This resets the hardware into a known state.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 1418 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

1419 {
1420  u32 ctrl;
1421  s32 ret_val;
1422 
1423  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_reset_hw_82575");
1424 
1425  /*
1426  * Prevent the PCI-E bus from sticking if there is no TLP connection
1427  * on the last TLP read/write transaction when MAC is reset.
1428  */
1429  ret_val = e1000_disable_pcie_master_generic(hw);
1430  if (ret_val)
1431  DEBUGOUT("PCI-E Master disable polling has failed.\n");
1432

1434  ret_val = e1000_set_pcie_completion_timeout(hw);
1435  if (ret_val)
1436  DEBUGOUT("PCI-E Set completion timeout has failed.\n");
1437 
1438  DEBUGOUT("Masking off all interrupts\n");

1440

1451

1453  if (ret_val) {
1454  /*
1455  * When auto config read does not complete, do not
1456  * return with an error. This can happen in situations
1457  * where there is no eeprom and prevents getting link.
1458  */
1459  DEBUGOUT("Auto Read Done did not complete\n");
1460  }
1461 
1462  /* If EEPROM is not present, run manual init scripts */
1463  if (!(E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_EECD) & E1000_EECD_PRES))
1464  e1000_reset_init_script_82575(hw);
1465

1467  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_IMC, 0xffffffff);
1468  E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICR);
1469 
1470  /* Install any alternate MAC address into RAR0 */
1471  ret_val = e1000_check_alt_mac_addr_generic(hw);
1472 
1473  return ret_val;
1474 }

static s32 e1000_reset_hw_82580 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_reset_hw_82580 - Reset hardware : pointer to the HW structure

This resets function or entire device (all ports, etc.) to a known state.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 2459 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

2460 {
2461  s32 ret_val = E1000_SUCCESS;
2462  /* BH SW mailbox bit in SW_FW_SYNC */
2463  u16 swmbsw_mask = E1000_SW_SYNCH_MB;
2464  u32 ctrl;
2465  bool global_device_reset = hw->dev_spec._82575.global_device_reset;
2466 
2467  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_reset_hw_82580");
2468 
2469  hw->dev_spec._82575.global_device_reset = false;
2470 
2471  /* 82580 does not reliably do global_device_reset due to hw errata */
2472  if (hw->mac.type == e1000_82580)
2473  global_device_reset = false;
2474 
2475  /* Get current control state. */
2476  ctrl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL);
2477 
2478  /*
2479  * Prevent the PCI-E bus from sticking if there is no TLP connection
2480  * on the last TLP read/write transaction when MAC is reset.
2481  */
2482  ret_val = e1000_disable_pcie_master_generic(hw);
2483  if (ret_val)
2484  DEBUGOUT("PCI-E Master disable polling has failed.\n");
2485 
2486  DEBUGOUT("Masking off all interrupts\n");
2487  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_IMC, 0xffffffff);
2488  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL, 0);
2489  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_TCTL, E1000_TCTL_PSP);
2490  E1000_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
2491 
2492  msec_delay(10);
2493 
2494  /* Determine whether or not a global dev reset is requested */
2495  if (global_device_reset && hw->mac.ops.acquire_swfw_sync(hw,
2496  swmbsw_mask))
2497  global_device_reset = false;
2498 
2499  if (global_device_reset && !(E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_STATUS) &
2500  E1000_STAT_DEV_RST_SET))
2501  ctrl |= E1000_CTRL_DEV_RST;
2502  else
2503  ctrl |= E1000_CTRL_RST;
2504 
2505  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL, ctrl);
2506 
2507  switch (hw->device_id) {
2508  case E1000_DEV_ID_DH89XXCC_SGMII:
2509  break;
2510  default:
2511  E1000_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
2512  break;
2513  }
2514 
2515  /* Add delay to insure DEV_RST or RST has time to complete */
2516  msec_delay(5);
2517 
2518  ret_val = e1000_get_auto_rd_done_generic(hw);
2519  if (ret_val) {
2520  /*
2521  * When auto config read does not complete, do not
2522  * return with an error. This can happen in situations
2523  * where there is no eeprom and prevents getting link.
2524  */
2525  DEBUGOUT("Auto Read Done did not complete\n");
2526  }
2527 
2528  /* clear global device reset status bit */
2529  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_STATUS, E1000_STAT_DEV_RST_SET);
2530 
2531  /* Clear any pending interrupt events. */
2532  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_IMC, 0xffffffff);
2533  E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ICR);
2534 
2535  ret_val = e1000_reset_mdicnfg_82580(hw);
2536  if (ret_val)
2537  DEBUGOUT("Could not reset MDICNFG based on EEPROM\n");
2538 
2539  /* Install any alternate MAC address into RAR0 */
2540  ret_val = e1000_check_alt_mac_addr_generic(hw);
2541 
2542  /* Release semaphore */
2543  if (global_device_reset)
2544  hw->mac.ops.release_swfw_sync(hw, swmbsw_mask);
2545 
2546  return ret_val;
2547 }

static s32 e1000_reset_mdicnfg_82580 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_reset_mdicnfg_82580 - Reset MDICNFG destination and com_mdio bits : pointer to the HW structure

This resets the the MDICNFG.Destination and MDICNFG.Com_MDIO bits based on the values found in the EEPROM. This addresses an issue in which these bits are not restored from EEPROM after reset.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 2421 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

2422 {
2423  s32 ret_val = E1000_SUCCESS;
2424  u32 mdicnfg;
2425  u16 nvm_data = 0;
2426 
2427  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_reset_mdicnfg_82580");
2428 
2429  if (hw->mac.type != e1000_82580)
2430  goto out;
2431  if (!e1000_sgmii_active_82575(hw))
2432  goto out;
2433 
2434  ret_val = hw->nvm.ops.read(hw, NVM_INIT_CONTROL3_PORT_A +
2435  NVM_82580_LAN_FUNC_OFFSET(hw->bus.func), 1,
2436  &nvm_data);
2437  if (ret_val) {
2438  DEBUGOUT("NVM Read Error\n");
2439  goto out;

void e1000_rx_fifo_flush_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)

e1000_rx_fifo_flush_82575 - Clean rx fifo after Rx enable : pointer to the HW structure

After Rx enable, if manageability is enabled then there is likely some bad data at the start of the fifo and possibly in the DMA fifo. This function clears the fifos and flushes any packets that came in as rx was being enabled.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 2144 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

2145 {
2146  u32 rctl, rlpml, rxdctl[4], rfctl, temp_rctl, rx_enabled;
2147  int i, ms_wait;
2148 
2149  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_rx_fifo_flush_82575");
2150 
2151  /* disable IPv6 options as per hardware errata */
2152  rfctl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RFCTL);
2153  rfctl |= E1000_RFCTL_IPV6_EX_DIS;
2154  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RFCTL, rfctl);
2155 
2156  if (hw->mac.type != e1000_82575 ||
2157  !(E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_MANC) & E1000_MANC_RCV_TCO_EN))
2158  return;
2159 
2160  /* Disable all Rx queues */
2161  for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
2162  rxdctl[i] = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RXDCTL(i));
2163  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RXDCTL(i),
2164  rxdctl[i] & ~E1000_RXDCTL_QUEUE_ENABLE);
2165  }
2166  /* Poll all queues to verify they have shut down */
2167  for (ms_wait = 0; ms_wait < 10; ms_wait++) {
2168  msec_delay(1);
2169  rx_enabled = 0;
2170  for (i = 0; i < 4; i++)
2171  rx_enabled |= E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RXDCTL(i));
2172  if (!(rx_enabled & E1000_RXDCTL_QUEUE_ENABLE))
2173  break;
2174  }
2175 
2176  if (ms_wait == 10)
2177  DEBUGOUT("Queue disable timed out after 10ms\n");
2178 
2179  /* Clear RLPML, RCTL.SBP, RFCTL.LEF, and set RCTL.LPE so that all
2180  * incoming packets are rejected. Set enable and wait 2ms so that
2181  * any packet that was coming in as RCTL.EN was set is flushed
2182  */
2183  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RFCTL, rfctl & ~E1000_RFCTL_LEF);
2184 
2185  rlpml = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RLPML);
2186  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RLPML, 0);
2187 
2188  rctl = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL);
2189  temp_rctl = rctl & ~(E1000_RCTL_EN | E1000_RCTL_SBP);
2190  temp_rctl |= E1000_RCTL_LPE;
2191 
2192  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL, temp_rctl);
2193  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL, temp_rctl | E1000_RCTL_EN);
2194  E1000_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
2195  msec_delay(2);
2196 
2197  /* Enable Rx queues that were previously enabled and restore our
2198  * previous state
2199  */
2200  for (i = 0; i < 4; i++)
2201  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RXDCTL(i), rxdctl[i]);
2202  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RCTL, rctl);
2203  E1000_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
2204 
2205  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RLPML, rlpml);
2206  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_RFCTL, rfctl);
2207 
2208  /* Flush receive errors generated by workaround */
2209  E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_ROC);
2210  E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_RNBC);
2211  E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_MPC);
2212 }

u16 e1000_rxpbs_adjust_82580 ( u32  data)

e1000_rxpbs_adjust_82580 - adjust RXPBS value to reflect actual Rx PBA size : data received by reading RXPBS register

The 82580 uses a table based approach for packet buffer allocation sizes. This function converts the retrieved value into the correct table value 0x0 0x1 0x2 0x3 0x4 0x5 0x6 0x7 0x0 36 72 144 1 2 4 8 16 0x8 35 70 140 rsv rsv rsv rsv rsv

static s32 e1000_set_d0_lplu_state_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw,
bool  active 
)
static

e1000_set_d0_lplu_state_82575 - Set Low Power Linkup D0 state : pointer to the HW structure : true to enable LPLU, false to disable

Sets the LPLU D0 state according to the active flag. When activating LPLU this function also disables smart speed and vice versa. LPLU will not be activated unless the device autonegotiation advertisement meets standards of either 10 or 10/100 or 10/100/1000 at all duplexes. This is a function pointer entry point only called by PHY setup routines.

s32 e1000_set_d3_lplu_state_82580 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw,
bool  active 
)
static

e1000_set_d3_lplu_state_82580 - Sets low power link up state for D3 : pointer to the HW structure : boolean used to enable/disable lplu

Success returns 0, Failure returns 1

The low power link up (lplu) state is set to the power management level D3 and SmartSpeed is disabled when active is true, else clear lplu for D3 and enable Smartspeed. LPLU and Smartspeed are mutually exclusive. LPLU is used during Dx states where the power conservation is most important. During driver activity, SmartSpeed should be enabled so performance is maintained.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 935 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

936 {
937  struct e1000_phy_info *phy = &hw->phy;

943 
944  if (!active) {
945  data &= ~E1000_82580_PM_D3_LPLU;
946  /*
947  * LPLU and SmartSpeed are mutually exclusive. LPLU is used
948  * during Dx states where the power conservation is most
949  * important. During driver activity we should enable
950  * SmartSpeed, so performance is maintained.
951  */
952  if (phy->smart_speed == e1000_smart_speed_on)
953  data |= E1000_82580_PM_SPD;
954  else if (phy->smart_speed == e1000_smart_speed_off)
955  data &= ~E1000_82580_PM_SPD;
956  } else if ((phy->autoneg_advertised == E1000_ALL_SPEED_DUPLEX) ||
957  (phy->autoneg_advertised == E1000_ALL_NOT_GIG) ||
958  (phy->autoneg_advertised == E1000_ALL_10_SPEED)) {
959  data |= E1000_82580_PM_D3_LPLU;
960  /* When LPLU is enabled, we should disable SmartSpeed */
961  data &= ~E1000_82580_PM_SPD;
962  }
963 
964  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_82580_PHY_POWER_MGMT, data);
965  return E1000_SUCCESS;
966 }

static s32 e1000_set_pcie_completion_timeout ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_set_pcie_completion_timeout - set pci-e completion timeout : pointer to the HW structure

The defaults for 82575 and 82576 should be in the range of 50us to 50ms, however the hardware default for these parts is 500us to 1ms which is less than the 10ms recommended by the pci-e spec. To address this we need to increase the value to either 10ms to 200ms for capability version 1 config, or 16ms to 55ms for version 2.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 2224 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

2225 {
2226  u32 gcr = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_GCR);
2227  s32 ret_val = E1000_SUCCESS;
2228  u16 pcie_devctl2;
2229 
2230  /* only take action if timeout value is defaulted to 0 */
2231  if (gcr & E1000_GCR_CMPL_TMOUT_MASK)
2232  goto out;
2233 
2234  /*
2235  * if capababilities version is type 1 we can write the
2236  * timeout of 10ms to 200ms through the GCR register
2237  */
2238  if (!(gcr & E1000_GCR_CAP_VER2)) {
2239  gcr |= E1000_GCR_CMPL_TMOUT_10ms;
2240  goto out;
2241  }
2242 
2243  /*
2244  * for version 2 capabilities we need to write the config space
2245  * directly in order to set the completion timeout value for
2246  * 16ms to 55ms
2247  */
2248  ret_val = e1000_read_pcie_cap_reg(hw, PCIE_DEVICE_CONTROL2,
2249  &pcie_devctl2);
2250  if (ret_val)
2251  goto out;
2252 
2253  pcie_devctl2 |= PCIE_DEVICE_CONTROL2_16ms;
2254 
2255  ret_val = e1000_write_pcie_cap_reg(hw, PCIE_DEVICE_CONTROL2,
2256  &pcie_devctl2);
2257 out:
2258  /* disable completion timeout resend */
2259  gcr &= ~E1000_GCR_CMPL_TMOUT_RESEND;
2260 
2261  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_GCR, gcr);
2262  return ret_val;
2263 }

static s32 e1000_set_sfp_media_type_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_set_sfp_media_type_82575 - derives SFP module media type. : pointer to the HW structure

The media type is chosen based on SFP module. compatibility flags retrieved from SFP ID EEPROM.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 1853 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

1854 {
1855  s32 ret_val = E1000_ERR_CONFIG;
1856  u32 ctrl_ext = 0;
1857  struct e1000_dev_spec_82575 *dev_spec = &hw->dev_spec._82575;
1858  struct sfp_e1000_flags *eth_flags = &dev_spec->eth_flags;
1859  u8 tranceiver_type = 0;
1860  s32 timeout = 3;
1861 
1862  /* Turn I2C interface ON and power on sfp cage */
1863  ctrl_ext = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT);
1864  ctrl_ext &= ~E1000_CTRL_EXT_SDP3_DATA;
1865  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT, ctrl_ext | E1000_CTRL_I2C_ENA);
1866 
1867  E1000_WRITE_FLUSH(hw);
1868 
1869  /* Read SFP module data */
1870  while (timeout) {
1871  ret_val = e1000_read_sfp_data_byte(hw,
1872  E1000_I2CCMD_SFP_DATA_ADDR(E1000_SFF_IDENTIFIER_OFFSET),
1873  &tranceiver_type);
1874  if (ret_val == E1000_SUCCESS)
1875  break;
1876  msec_delay(100);
1877  timeout--;
1878  }
1879  if (ret_val != E1000_SUCCESS)
1880  goto out;
1881 
1882  ret_val = e1000_read_sfp_data_byte(hw,
1883  E1000_I2CCMD_SFP_DATA_ADDR(E1000_SFF_ETH_FLAGS_OFFSET),
1884  (u8 *)eth_flags);
1885  if (ret_val != E1000_SUCCESS)
1886  goto out;
1887 
1888  /* Check if there is some SFP module plugged and powered */
1889  if ((tranceiver_type == E1000_SFF_IDENTIFIER_SFP) ||
1890  (tranceiver_type == E1000_SFF_IDENTIFIER_SFF)) {
1891  dev_spec->module_plugged = true;
1892  if (eth_flags->e1000_base_lx || eth_flags->e1000_base_sx) {
1893  hw->phy.media_type = e1000_media_type_internal_serdes;
1894  } else if (eth_flags->e100_base_fx) {
1895  dev_spec->sgmii_active = true;
1896  hw->phy.media_type = e1000_media_type_internal_serdes;
1897  } else if (eth_flags->e1000_base_t) {
1898  dev_spec->sgmii_active = true;
1899  hw->phy.media_type = e1000_media_type_copper;
1900  } else {
1901  hw->phy.media_type = e1000_media_type_unknown;
1902  DEBUGOUT("PHY module has not been recognized\n");
1903  goto out;
1904  }
1905  } else {
1906  hw->phy.media_type = e1000_media_type_unknown;
1907  }
1908  ret_val = E1000_SUCCESS;
1909 out:
1910  /* Restore I2C interface setting */
1911  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT, ctrl_ext);
1912  return ret_val;
1913 }
out

static s32 e1000_setup_copper_link_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_setup_copper_link_82575 - Configure copper link settings : pointer to the HW structure

Configures the link for auto-neg or forced speed and duplex. Then we check for link, once link is established calls to configure collision distance and flow control are called.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 1539 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

1548  ctrl |= E1000_CTRL_SLU;
1549  ctrl &= ~(E1000_CTRL_FRCSPD | E1000_CTRL_FRCDPX);

static s32 e1000_setup_serdes_link_82575 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_setup_serdes_link_82575 - Setup link for serdes : pointer to the HW structure

Configure the physical coding sub-layer (PCS) link. The PCS link is used on copper connections where the serialized gigabit media independent interface (sgmii), or serdes fiber is being used. Configures the link for auto-negotiation or forces speed/duplex.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 1625 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

1626 {
1627  u32 ctrl_ext, ctrl_reg, reg, anadv_reg;
1628  bool pcs_autoneg;
1629  s32 ret_val = E1000_SUCCESS;
1630  u16 data;
1631 
1632  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_setup_serdes_link_82575");
1633 
1634  if ((hw->phy.media_type != e1000_media_type_internal_serdes) &&
1635  !e1000_sgmii_active_82575(hw))
1636  return ret_val;
1637 
1638  /*
1639  * On the 82575, SerDes loopback mode persists until it is
1640  * explicitly turned off or a power cycle is performed. A read to
1641  * the register does not indicate its status. Therefore, we ensure
1642  * loopback mode is disabled during initialization.
1643  */
1644  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_SCTL, E1000_SCTL_DISABLE_SERDES_LOOPBACK);
1645 
1646  /* power on the sfp cage if present */
1647  ctrl_ext = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT);
1648  ctrl_ext &= ~E1000_CTRL_EXT_SDP3_DATA;
1649  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL_EXT, ctrl_ext);
1650 
1651  ctrl_reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL);
1652  ctrl_reg |= E1000_CTRL_SLU;
1653 
1654  /* set both sw defined pins on 82575/82576*/
1655  if (hw->mac.type == e1000_82575 || hw->mac.type == e1000_82576)
1656  ctrl_reg |= E1000_CTRL_SWDPIN0 | E1000_CTRL_SWDPIN1;
1657 
1658  reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PCS_LCTL);
1659 
1660  /* default pcs_autoneg to the same setting as mac autoneg */
1661  pcs_autoneg = hw->mac.autoneg;
1662 
1663  switch (ctrl_ext & E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_MASK) {
1664  case E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_SGMII:
1665  /* sgmii mode lets the phy handle forcing speed/duplex */
1666  pcs_autoneg = true;
1667  /* autoneg time out should be disabled for SGMII mode */
1668  reg &= ~(E1000_PCS_LCTL_AN_TIMEOUT);
1669  break;
1670  case E1000_CTRL_EXT_LINK_MODE_1000BASE_KX:
1671  /* disable PCS autoneg and support parallel detect only */
1672  pcs_autoneg = false;
1673  /* fall through to default case */
1674  default:
1675  if (hw->mac.type == e1000_82575 ||
1676  hw->mac.type == e1000_82576) {
1677  ret_val = hw->nvm.ops.read(hw, NVM_COMPAT, 1, &data);
1678  if (ret_val) {
1679  DEBUGOUT("NVM Read Error\n");
1680  return ret_val;
1681  }
1682 
1683  if (data & E1000_EEPROM_PCS_AUTONEG_DISABLE_BIT)
1684  pcs_autoneg = false;
1685  }
1686 
1687  /*
1688  * non-SGMII modes only supports a speed of 1000/Full for the
1689  * link so it is best to just force the MAC and let the pcs
1690  * link either autoneg or be forced to 1000/Full
1691  */
1692  ctrl_reg |= E1000_CTRL_SPD_1000 | E1000_CTRL_FRCSPD |
1693  E1000_CTRL_FD | E1000_CTRL_FRCDPX;
1694 
1695  /* set speed of 1000/Full if speed/duplex is forced */
1696  reg |= E1000_PCS_LCTL_FSV_1000 | E1000_PCS_LCTL_FDV_FULL;
1697  break;
1698  }
1699 
1700  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_CTRL, ctrl_reg);
1701 
1702  /*
1703  * New SerDes mode allows for forcing speed or autonegotiating speed
1704  * at 1gb. Autoneg should be default set by most drivers. This is the
1705  * mode that will be compatible with older link partners and switches.
1706  * However, both are supported by the hardware and some drivers/tools.
1707  */
1708  reg &= ~(E1000_PCS_LCTL_AN_ENABLE | E1000_PCS_LCTL_FLV_LINK_UP |
1709  E1000_PCS_LCTL_FSD | E1000_PCS_LCTL_FORCE_LINK);
1710 
1711  if (pcs_autoneg) {
1712  /* Set PCS register for autoneg */
1713  reg |= E1000_PCS_LCTL_AN_ENABLE | /* Enable Autoneg */
1714  E1000_PCS_LCTL_AN_RESTART; /* Restart autoneg */
1715 
1716  /* Disable force flow control for autoneg */
1717  reg &= ~E1000_PCS_LCTL_FORCE_FCTRL;
1718 
1719  /* Configure flow control advertisement for autoneg */
1720  anadv_reg = E1000_READ_REG(hw, E1000_PCS_ANADV);
1721  anadv_reg &= ~(E1000_TXCW_ASM_DIR | E1000_TXCW_PAUSE);
1722 
1723  switch (hw->fc.requested_mode) {
1724  case e1000_fc_full:
1725  case e1000_fc_rx_pause:
1726  anadv_reg |= E1000_TXCW_ASM_DIR;
1727  anadv_reg |= E1000_TXCW_PAUSE;
1728  break;
1729  case e1000_fc_tx_pause:
1730  anadv_reg |= E1000_TXCW_ASM_DIR;
1731  break;
1732  default:
1733  break;
1734  }
1735 
1736  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_PCS_ANADV, anadv_reg);
1737 
1738  DEBUGOUT1("Configuring Autoneg:PCS_LCTL=0x%08X\n", reg);
1739  } else {
1740  /* Set PCS register for forced link */
1741  reg |= E1000_PCS_LCTL_FSD; /* Force Speed */
1742 
1743  /* Force flow control for forced link */
1744  reg |= E1000_PCS_LCTL_FORCE_FCTRL;
1745 
1746  DEBUGOUT1("Configuring Forced Link:PCS_LCTL=0x%08X\n", reg);
1747  }
1748 
1749  E1000_WRITE_REG(hw, E1000_PCS_LCTL, reg);
1750 
1751  if (!pcs_autoneg && !e1000_sgmii_active_82575(hw))
1752  e1000_force_mac_fc_generic(hw);
1753 
1754  return ret_val;
1755 }

e1000_shutdown_serdes_link_82575 - Remove link during power down : pointer to the HW structure

In the case of serdes shut down sfp and PCS on driver unload when management pass thru is not enabled.

static s32 e1000_update_nvm_checksum_82580 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_update_nvm_checksum_82580 - Update EEPROM checksum : pointer to the HW structure

Updates the EEPROM section checksums for all 4 ports by reading/adding each word of the EEPROM up to the checksum. Then calculates the EEPROM checksum and writes the value to the EEPROM.

e1000_82575.c 파일의 2690 번째 라인에서 정의되었습니다.

2691 {
2692  s32 ret_val;
2693  u16 j, nvm_data;
2694  u16 nvm_offset;
2695 
2696  DEBUGFUNC("e1000_update_nvm_checksum_82580");
2697 
2698  ret_val = hw->nvm.ops.read(hw, NVM_COMPATIBILITY_REG_3, 1, &nvm_data);
2699  if (ret_val) {
2700  DEBUGOUT("NVM Read Error while updating checksum compatibility bit.\n");
2701  goto out;
2702  }
2703 
2704  if (!(nvm_data & NVM_COMPATIBILITY_BIT_MASK)) {
2705  /* set compatibility bit to validate checksums appropriately */
2706  nvm_data = nvm_data | NVM_COMPATIBILITY_BIT_MASK;
2707  ret_val = hw->nvm.ops.write(hw, NVM_COMPATIBILITY_REG_3, 1,
2708  &nvm_data);
2709  if (ret_val) {
2710  DEBUGOUT("NVM Write Error while updating checksum compatibility bit.\n");
2711  goto out;
2712  }
2713  }
2714 
2715  for (j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
2716  nvm_offset = NVM_82580_LAN_FUNC_OFFSET(j);
2717  ret_val = e1000_update_nvm_checksum_with_offset(hw, nvm_offset);
2718  if (ret_val)
2719  goto out;
2720  }
2721 
2722 out:
2723  return ret_val;
2724 }

)

e1000_update_nvm_checksum_with_offset - Update EEPROM checksum : pointer to the HW structure : offset in words of the checksum protected region

Updates the EEPROM checksum by reading/adding each word of the EEPROM up to the checksum. Then calculates the EEPROM checksum and writes the value to the EEPROM.

static s32 e1000_validate_nvm_checksum_82580 ( struct e1000_hw *  hw)
static

e1000_validate_nvm_checksum_82580 - Validate EEPROM checksum : pointer to the HW structure

Calculates the EEPROM section checksum by reading/adding each word of the EEPROM and then verifies that the sum of the EEPROM is equal to 0xBABA.

2661  goto out;
